sourcesContent:
import React from "react";
import GamerDetails from "./GamerDetails";

import Navbar from "./Navbar";
import { Row, Col } from "react-bootstrap";
import image from "./images/i3"

const gproducts = [

  {
      id: "1",
      image: "./images/i3.png",
      name: "Intel® Core™ i3-XXXX Processor (3M Cache, up to 3.10 GHz)",
      description: "The best processing chip for entry level computing",
      brand: "Intel Computers",
      category: 'Processors',
      price: 2,
      countInStock: 15,
      rating: 5,
      numReviews: 10,

  },

  {
      id: "2",
      name: "GTX 750Ti",
      description: "Start your journey with an exciting integration of several CUDA cores packed in a single chip",
      brand: "Nvidia",
      category: 'Graphics Card',
      price: 3,
      countInStock: 10,
      rating: 5,
      numReviews: 10,

  },

  {
      id: "3",
      name: "H310M-S2",
      description: "The Best Entry-Level motherboard you would ever find!",
      brand: "Gigabyte",
      category: 'Motherboard',
      price: 2,
      countInStock: 15,
      rating: 5,
      numReviews: 10,

  },

  {
      id: "4",
      name: "HyperX 1x8GB 1600MHZ RAM Stick",
      description: "The Best Entry-Level Random Access Memory you would ever find!",
      brand: "Kingston",
      category: 'Memory',
      price: 2,
      countInStock: 15,
      rating: 5,
      numReviews: 10,

  },

  {
      id: "5",
      name: "Seagate Firecuda 500GB Hard Drive",
      description: "Your Operating System and other files under one roof!",
      brand: "Seagate",
      category: 'Space',
      price: 2,
      countInStock: 15,
      rating: 5,
      numReviews: 10,

  },
]

export function Gamer() {
  return (
    <>
      <Navbar />
      <Row>
        {gproducts.map((gproduct) => (
          <Col>
            <GamerDetails gproduct={gproduct} />
          </Col>
        ))}
      </Row>
    </>
  );
}
